The paper presents a method for using Deep Q-Networks (DQNs) in multi-objective environments, which involves learning from high-level visual state representations. This suggests that the paper could belong to the sub-categories of Machine Learning (cs.LG), Artificial Intelligence (cs.AI), Robotics (cs.RO), Computer Vision (cs.CV), and Game Theory (cs.GT). Among these, Machine Learning and Artificial Intelligence are the most likely categories as they are directly related to the proposed method. Robotics and Computer Vision are also relevant as the paper uses a game-like simulator with high-level visual input. Game Theory is less likely but still possible as the paper deals with multiple objectives in a game-like environment.
